that Chumhum bought it?

41:00.590 --> 41:02.888
I don't know what it is, but
we didn't do anything wrong.

41:02.920 --> 41:05.559
Business just does
what business does, Alicia.

41:05.590 --> 41:08.889
And we're now running late
for a partners' meeting.

41:08.930 --> 41:10.795
DAVID:
Good!

41:10.830 --> 41:14.095
Ah, the executive committee
has arrived.

41:14.130 --> 41:15.893
How is it going?

41:15.940 --> 41:17.134
I've presented
our plan

41:17.170 --> 41:20.003
to the partnership, and I
think we've come to a consensus

41:20.040 --> 41:22.907
on how to handle the
clerical rebellion of 2013.

41:24.980 --> 41:26.504
I'd appreciate
at least being able

41:26.550 --> 41:28.768
to speak on behalf
of the assistants?
It's okay.

41:28.820 --> 41:30.845
We had another idea
on how to handle this.

41:30.880 --> 41:32.518
In addition
to their responsibilities

41:32.550 --> 41:33.778
supporting you and David,

41:33.820 --> 41:36.084
Lorna and Margie have both been
appointed staff coordinators.

41:36.120 --> 41:37.815
DAVID:
And while I'm sure we're both

41:37.860 --> 41:39.953
gonna miss their very friendly
faces around the firm,

41:39.990 --> 41:42.094
we're allowing them to
telecommute three days a week.

41:42.130 --> 41:44.667
WILL:
You asked us to listen,
so we listened.

41:44.700 --> 41:46.691
And this is what
they really wanted.

41:46.730 --> 41:47.890
And the other employees?

41:47.930 --> 41:49.238
We'll get to them in time.
Baby steps.

41:49.270 --> 41:52.933
You bought off
the ringleaders.

41:52.970 --> 41:54.631
We handled the problem

41:54.680 --> 41:57.137
in a way that protected
us and satisfied them.

41:57.180 --> 41:59.045
DAVID:
It's what management does.

41:59.080 --> 42:00.809
DIANE:
So,

42:00.850 --> 42:02.169
onto the next
order of busmess.

